**File:** tests/integration/web/routes/push.test.ts
**Lines:** 139-152
**Category:** Does Nothing
**Severity:** High

## Problem
Test "should return 500 when VAPID key not configured" (lines 139-152) is completely non-functional. It sets up an Express app but never sends any request to it, makes no assertions, and explicitly acknowledges it cannot work with the comment "would require module re-loading".

## Evidence
```typescript
it('should return 500 when VAPID key not configured', async () => {
  const originalKey = process.env.VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY;
  process.env.VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY = '';

  const testApp = express();
  testApp.use(express.json());

  // Re-import router to pick up empty key
  // Note: In practice, this would require module re-loading
  // For this test, we'll just verify the endpoint exists

  process.env.VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY = originalKey;
  // ← No request sent, no assertions made!
});
```

## Implementation Instructions
**Option A: Implement properly using jest.resetModules()**
```typescript
it('should return 500 when VAPID key not configured', async () => {
  // Save and clear
  const originalKey = process.env.VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY;
  process.env.VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY = '';

  // Reset module cache
  jest.resetModules();

  // Re-import with empty key
  const { createPushRouter } = await import('@/web/routes/push.js');
  const testApp = express();
  testApp.use(express.json());
  testApp.use('/api/push', createPushRouter());

  // Make request
  const response = await request(testApp).get('/api/push/vapid-public-key');
  expect(response.status).toBe(500);

  // Restore
  process.env.VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY = originalKey;
});
```

**Option B: Remove the test** if this behavior cannot be tested

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Test either makes actual HTTP request and asserts 500 status
- [ ] OR test is removed with comment explaining why
- [ ] No empty tests that make no assertions

